                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.13/14.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 14, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>President Gomez to-day returned the amnesty bill to Congress recommending that it
                    be amended so as to cover only political offenses but without prejudice to right
                    of Congress later to consider grant of amnesty for the other crimes the present
                    bill covers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Beaupré</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
